    <section id="rasterbator" class="research_article">
        <h2>The Rasterbator</h2>
        <figure>
            <a href="http://arje.net/rasterbator"><i class="icon icon--l icon-rasterbator"></i></a>
        </figure>
        <p>I took the liberty to update the <a href="http://arje.net/rasterbator">Rasterbator</a> to run on my MacBook Pro.
        On MacOS it requires the <a href="http://go-mono.com/">Mono-Framework</a> to work, under Windows XP you will need an installed .NET-framework.
        If you find a bug or have a comment, please write me an email.</p>
        <p>What it does? The Rasterbator creates huge, rasterized, multi-page images from any picture.
        The rasterized images can be printed and assembled into extremely cool posters. </p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="files/nsis/The%20Rasterbator%20v1.3.dmg">MacOS DiskImage</a> v1.3 (dmg, 709 KB, 12.03.2010)</li>
            <li><a href="files/nsis/The%20Rasterbator%20v1.3%20setup.exe">Windows Installer</a> v1.3 (exe, 467 KB, 12.03.2010)</li>
            <li>The current source (v1.4.2) is hosted at <a class="extern" href="https://github.com/rejas/rasterbator">github</a>.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

